Class DeviceMapChangelog

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kontakt.sdk.core.data.changelog.AbstractMapChangelog<UUID,Device>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.kontakt.sdk.core.interfaces.changelog.MapChangelog<UUID,Device>
    Deprecated.

    @Deprecated
public class DeviceMapChangelog
extends com.kontakt.sdk.core.data.changelog.AbstractMapChangelog<UUID,Device>
    Map Changelogs act as maps where the keys are requested characteristic properties of elements and values are Changelogs consisting of added, modified and deleted elements. In order to obtain Map Changelog you must request by with REST client (KontaktApiClient) Beacon Map Changelog contains Beacon Changelogs for specified venue Ids. The venue Ids are the backed map keys whereas the Beacon Changelogs are the values. Changelogs in Android SDK v1.0.6 are deprecated and will be removed in the next versions.
